# frontend/ — React 18 SPA Frontend

## Purpose
Single-page application for admin dashboard, auction pages, chat, and payment status.
The regular buyer/seller UI (product listing, cart, checkout) is served by PHP views — this React
app only covers features requiring real-time interactivity or complex admin UI.

## Framework & Libraries
- React 18.2 + TypeScript
- Vite (build tool, dev server with proxy)
- TailwindCSS + PostCSS
- React Router v6 (client-side routing)
- Axios (HTTP client)
- Socket.io-client (WebSocket connection to node-server)

## Entry Point
frontend/src/main.tsx → renders <App /> into #root in index.html

## Directory Map
```
frontend/src/
├── App.tsx             Route definitions (React Router v6)
├── context/
│   └── AuthContext.tsx Global auth state — wraps app, provides useAuth() hook
├── hooks/
│   ├── useAuctionSocket.ts  Socket.io hook for auction room events
│   ├── useAuctionTimer.ts   Countdown timer for auction end
│   └── useChatSocket.ts     Socket.io hook for chat events
├── services/
│   ├── auth.ts              Auth API calls (login, register, profile)
│   ├── notification.ts      Push notification subscription management
│   ├── socketClient.ts      Socket.io client singleton
│   ├── api/                 Axios instance + API endpoint functions
│   ├── routes/              Route path constants
│   └── utils/               Shared utility functions
├── views/
│   ├── components/
│   │   └── layouts/         AdminLayout, MainLayout (wraps pages)
│   └── pages/
│       ├── admin/           AdminLogin, AdminDashboard, AdminReviews
│       ├── auction/         AuctionList, AuctionDetail (real-time bidding)
│       ├── chat/            ChatPage (real-time messaging)
│       └── PaymentStatus.tsx (Midtrans redirect landing page)
├── types/
│   ├── css.d.ts             CSS module type declarations
│   └── socket.ts            Socket.io event type definitions
└── utils/
    └── imageUtils.ts        Image URL helpers (maps to /uploads/* paths)
```

## React Routes (App.tsx)
- /admin/login          → AdminLogin
- /admin/dashboard      → AdminDashboard (protected, requires admin JWT)
- /admin/reviews        → AdminReviews (protected)
- /auction              → AuctionList
- /auction/:id          → AuctionDetail (Socket.io bid room)
- /chat                 → ChatPage (Socket.io chat)
- /payment/status       → PaymentStatus
- *                     → NotFound

## Colour Palette (main: #00AA5B)
- #00AA5B — primary green (buttons, active, links)
- #008f4d — hover/dark green
- #007a42 — darker green (gradient end)
- #005c2e — deep green (dark text)
- #e6f7ef — light green bg (replaces blue-50)
- #ccf0de — medium light green (replaces blue-100)
- #99e1bd — soft green border (replaces blue-200)
- #1a3d2b — dark footer bg

## Auth
JWT-based (not session). AuthContext stores token in localStorage.
Protected routes redirect to /admin/login if no valid JWT.
Token sent as Authorization: Bearer <token> header to Node.js API.

## API Targets
- /api/node/* → proxied to Node.js (Fastify) during dev (vite.config.js proxy)
- In production: nginx routes /api/node/* to node-server:3000
- VITE_API_BASE_URL env var sets the base URL (default: http://localhost:8080)

## Build Output
`npm run build` → frontend/dist/
Docker build (Dockerfile.nginx) copies frontend/ → builds → puts in nginx container at /var/www/html/public/
For dev outside Docker: cd frontend && npm run dev (Vite HMR at localhost:5173)
